      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m concerned you\u0027re using ANDROID_CPU_ACCELERATION_XXX values as part of the protocol between the emulator and Android Studio, this could very easily break if someone changes the declarations of the values.\n\nPlease add a big WARNING where these constants are declared to indicate that their order should not be touched, and that no value should be removed from the list due to this.\n\nAlternatively, consider returning a textual message instead.",
      "revId": "a28510abbc04bc01ad8bd28010885bb3797a8607",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
